Local Supersymmetry  

In this section we consider hypermultiplets coupled to 
supergravity with a certain number of commuting target space isometries.
This property we then use to dualize the corresponding scalars into
tensors, just as we did for rigid supersymmetry. In this way, we find
the most general locally  supersymmetric system of scalars and
tensors (with at most two derivatives and undeformed gauge
transformations).

For local  supersymmetry, the  real hypermultiplet scalars
parametrize a quaternionic manifold. The holonomy group of
such manifolds is contained in ,
with a nonvanishing Sp(1) connection.

